commText: Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. M Siddharth will open the attack
M Siddharth to Kohli, no run, short of length around off, Kohli knocks it into the off-side and searches for his first run, not there
M Siddharth to Kohli, 1 run, short and sliding in, Kohli is cramped on the pull and mistimes it wide of mid-on
M Siddharth to du Plessis, no run, I0$ dart on off-stump, Faf stays leg-side and knocks it to cover-point
M Siddharth to du Plessis, 1 run, I0$ slower and around off, Faf eases it to long-off

Krunal Pandya, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

These two batters along with Maxwell have generally struggled against slow bowling and left-arm spin in particular, hence LSG have started with two left-arm spinners from both ends. Also the pitch is aiding the slow bowlers..
M Siddharth to du Plessis, 1 run, flatter and drifting in, Faf knocks it to long-off
M Siddharth to Kohli, no run, short and around off, Kohli makes room and cracks it to cover-point, straight to the fielder
M Siddharth to Kohli, 1 run, short of length and slanting in, Kohli tucks it into the vacant mid-wicket region. This was bowled at I0$

M Siddharth to du Plessis, 2 runs, in the air and just short of Bishnoi. Faf comes down the track and is deceived in flight, Siddharth slowed it up and had Faf checking his shot, the ball goes uppishly towards cover-point and Bishnoi dives forward, the ball beats him and the pair scamper back for the second

M Siddharth to du Plessis, FOUR, that's smart batting. Siddharth is darting them in from short of length, so Faf decides to stay leg-side of the ball and belt the pull straight past Kohli, no chance for mid-on
M Siddharth to du Plessis, FOUR, even better. Siddharth offers a bit of space around off and Faf pounces on it, he stays leg-side and punches it in front of square past a diving extra cover

There's a wide slip in place

Naveen-ul-Haq to Kohli, SIX, stand and smash into the sightscreen. Good length ball around off, Kohli had the room to free his hands and he lofts through the line. Struck it straight and had no problem clearing the rope
Naveen-ul-Haq to Kohli, 1 run, dipping full toss and Kohli was almost deceived, he delays his bat swing at the last second and heaves it to mid-wicket
Naveen-ul-Haq to du Plessis, no run, I0$ in-slanter and Faf is cramped for room, ekes out an inside edge onto the pad and the ball rolls back

Naveen-ul-Haq to du Plessis, FOUR, now Faf's turn to stand and deliver. Angled in nicely into the arc and Faf just swings through the line, clears mid-on with ease and the ball bounces only once before crossing the rope
M Siddharth to Kohli, FOUR, I0$ short of length around off, Kohli makes room and cracks the cut square on the off-side, pierced the packed off-side field with precision
M Siddharth to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

M Siddharth to Kohli, out Caught by Padikkal!! The TN spinner is off on a celebratory run. It is his maiden IPL wicket and it is the big one of Kohli. Why wouldn't you be elated? This is a massive breakthrough for LSG in the powerplay as Kohli has been RCB's go-to batter this season. This was bowled smartly. Slowed it up and drew Kohli into the big shot, the ball turned away and caught the outer half, the ball skies to backward point and Padikkal back tracks a few steps to take the catch. Kohli vs left arm spin in IPL 2024 - 33 balls | 28 runs | One dismissal | SR 84.84
Here's Mayank Yadav. Buckle up folks this is going to be fast and furious..

Mayank Yadav to du Plessis, out du Plessis Run Out!! Wow! Brilliant work from Padikkal. Both openers sent back in succession and LSG are cock-a-hoop. Angled in and Faf turns it to mid-wicket, straight to Padikkal and he sets off on a non-existent single, Padikkal gets a good bounce to gather the ball and then has one stump to aim, he hits the target and Faf is not even in the frame. du Plessis run out (Padikkal) 19(13) [4s-3]

Mayank Yadav to Maxwell, out Caught by Pooran!! There's Mayank and his pace. He accounted for three Punjab batters in the same way and Maxwell is his latest victim. 151ks short of length delivery and Maxwell is rushed on the pull, the ball hits the higher part of the bat and balloons in front of mid-on, Pooran runs in and completes the dolly. Maxwell woeful start with the bat this season extends to another game. RCB are in trouble. Maxwell c Pooran b Mayank Yadav 0(2)

Highlights (1-6 overs) - Siddharth bowls a tight 3-run first over - Left-arms spin at both ends as Krunal shares new ball - Siddharth almost gets Faf but the latter smacks successive fours in a 12-run over - RCB greet Naveen with a 11-run over - Siddharth forces a mishit and gets Virat to silence Chinnaswamy - Stunning direct-hit from DDP sees Faf walk back - Mayank Yadav outsarts Maxwell with a 151kph ball

23:10 Local Time, 17:40 GMT, 23:10 IST: KL Rahul has a bright smile on his face and so does coach Justin Langer in the dug-out who is seen hugging Mayank Yadav. Clinical performance from the visitors. Inserted to bat, they posted an above-par total on a two-paced trick. The RCB bowlers had their moments but QdK's half-ton, Stoinis's cameo in the middle overs and Pooran's five sixes in the death overs resulted in LSG crossing 180. In the second innings, LSG started with two left-arm spinners against Faf and Kohli. Siddharth started well by bowling quick and not offering any width. The RCB openers adjusted and the 25-year-old conceded three boundaries on the trot. However, the TN spinner smartly bowled one slowly to nip out the in-form Kohli. Mayank Yadav, the pace sensation, was introduced in the final over of the powerplay and he wasted little time to get into the act. Suicidal running coupled with Padikkal's brilliance resulted in Faf's dismissal and Maxwell was nipped out for a duck by Mayank who troubled the big-hitter with pace and bounce. The 21-year-old added one more wicket in his following over as he castled the other Aussie all-rounder. And, RCB were reduced to 58/4 in the eighth over.

Patidar and Rawat stitched a 36-run stand but they never threatened LSG. Mahipal Lomror, the Impact Player, came out all guns blazing and scored a quickfire 33 but with his dismissal any hopes (however tiny) of an RCB win extinguished. Lucknow were definitely the better team in all three facets of the game today and the margin of win says it all. Stick around for the presentations...

Faf du Plessis | RCB captain: Spot on (dropped catches cost us). Two very good players, QdK when was on 25-30 and Nicky P was on 2, 60-65 extra runs, mistakes like that can cost you in the IPL. It is the new action you haven't faced before, and if they have pace then you need time to get used to it (about Mayank). But his ability to control length and have accuracy is impressive. I didn't think we were very good with our bowling especially in the powerplay, Maxwell brought it back and there were some pleasing signs in the death overs. You need two guys to bat through and get a partnership which we were not able to do. We need the strong characters in the dressing room to put their hand up.

Quinton de Kock: It (pitch) was holding and bouncing. Wanted to bat for longer because we lost wickets at times. He is bowling rockets in our team. He is keeping it simple and doing really well for his team. That's why he (Pooran) gets the big bucks I guess (On opponents not being able to keep Pooran quiet). Conditions are never quite the same as an opener if you have played at the same venue before.

KL Rahul | LSG captain: Overall a really good performance. The wicket was a bit tricky, there was some help for the seamers, it was slightly on the sticky side. We got off to a really good start, Quinton gave us a really good start. By the time the opposition found out what were the lengths to hit, we had gotten away with the game and had probably 10-15 runs ahead of what we needed to be. That's what helped us in the back end though they bowled really well in the back end. The chat was very simple - there's a bit help in the wicket, try and use the wicket, not go to the yorkers really quickly. Here in Chinnaswamy, the pressure can come on you really quickly with one or two fours/sixes in an over, just changes everything. It's important to stay calm and keep trusting that the wicket will help us. One ball hit me really hard, so happy to see Mayank bowl the way he's been bowling in the last couple of games. He's quietly patiently waited for two seasons in the dug-out, missed out last year because of injury unfortunately. But he's been in Bombay with the physios working really hard. He understands that bowling 155 is not easy and in a young age, he's had a few injuries. He's really professional in looking after his body, it's really good to see and has a great temperament. Enjoying seeing him bowl from probably 20 yards behind the stumps, that's where I'd like to be when he's bowling. I am always tempted to bowl first, that's generally been the trend in T20 cricket. If I have a look at our record, it speaks differently. The good thing that I am doing is losing the toss, that really helps. If we get bowled out or if the opposition blasts us out of the game, then there's something to go back and think about. If we are doing most things right ... it's okay to lose sometimes, the opposition is also going to turn up on the ground and want to win. We don't really stress too much about it. The first game was one such game, we tried really hard, they bowled better than us. We have bounced back really well. This is how we generally play our cricket. Powerplay bowling has always been a question mark for us in the two seasons that we have played, trying to fix that. We've gone spin this game, very obvious match-up against RCB which worked. We'll try to find ways to get those wickets in the powerplay.

Mayank Yadav | Player of the Match: Feel really good, two Player of the Match awards in two matches. I am happier that we won both the matches. My goal is to play for the country. I feel this is just the start. I enjoyed Cameron Green's wicket the most. There are a lot of factors to bowl quick - diet, sleep, training. I am focusing a lot on my diet and recovery - ice bath.

Back-to-back Player of the Match awards for Mayank Yadav! Two fiery three-fers in as many IPL matches and the speedster is also rushing batters who have grown up on fast pitches. That's such a rare and a great sight to see especially in this format where the bowlers are mere cannon fodder on many occasions. LSG jump up to the fourth spot with their second consecutive win and they know how to defend totals. They seem to have a pretty settled line-up which bodes well for Rahul and Co. RCB, on the other hand, have now lost three of their four matches which includes back-to-back losses at home. Yash Dayal's performance with the ball and Lomror's blitz are the only positives from this game. While a lot of talk has been on their bowling, their famed batting line-up is yet to fire as a unit. They are currently placed second from bottom and it's time to bring curtains on this encounter. Tune in tomorrow for I0$ Until then, it's goodbye from Abhinand Raghavendran, Akshay Maanay, Ramakrishnan MS and Praveen
